body:
The specification means a client has to generate:
- [ ] Client Application cancelled the request: CANCELLED
- [ ] Deadline expires before server returns status: DEADLINE_EXCEEDED
- [ ] No response received before Deadline expires. This may occur either when the client is unable to send the request to the server or when the server fails to respond in time.: DEADLINE_EXCEEDED
- [ ] Some data transmitted (e.g., request metadata written to TCP connection) before connection breaks: UNAVAILABLE
- [ ] Could not decompress, but compression algorithm supported (Server -> Client): INTERNAL
- [ ] Flow-control protocol violation: INTERNAL
- [ ] Error parsing returned status: UNKNOWN
- [ ] Incorrect Auth metadata ( Credentials failed to get metadata, Incompatible credentials set on channel and call, Invalid host set in `:authority` metadata, etc.): UNAUTHENTICATED
- [ ] Error parsing response proto: INTERNAL

And not generate any of:
- [ ] INVALID_ARGUMENT
- [ ] NOT_FOUND
- [ ] ALREADY_EXISTS
- [ ] FAILED_PRECONDITION
- [ ] ABORTED
- [ ] OUT_OF_RANGE
- [ ] DATA_LOSS
@muxi - Please paste code snippet links that show the error generation for each of these.

Here is a checklist of current status of this issue. Will keep it updated as each of them gets fixed
- [x] ([code](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/a9df5d1029b303a305481c4bb765c6bed2e8ebbb/src/objective-c/GRPCClient/GRPCCall.m#L163-L165)) Client Application Cancelled the request: CANCELLED
- [x] (Not implemented) Deadline expires before server returns status: DEADLINE_EXCEEDED
- [x] (Not implemented) No response received before Deadline expires. This may occur either when the client is unable to send the request to the server or when the server fails to respond in time.: DEADLINE_EXCEEDED
- [x] ([code](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/a9df5d1029b303a305481c4bb765c6bed2e8ebbb/src/objective-c/GRPCClient/GRPCCall.m#L377-L379)) Some data transmitted (e.g., request metadata written to TCP connection) before connection breaks: UNAVAILABLE
- [x] ([code](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/1f6faf3725453d45953b2a55feafd7a368f96fff/src/core/lib/surface/byte_buffer_reader.c#L68-L72), transferred to Issue #7149) Could not decompress, but compression algorithm supported (Server -> Client): INTERNAL
- [x] ([code](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/296340d4f136bd9a76f768f89dfd0107d6d8d70d/src/core/ext/transport/chttp2/transport/parsing.c#L238-L241)) Flow-control protocol violation: INTERNAL
- [x] ([code](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/1f6faf3725453d45953b2a55feafd7a368f96fff/src/core/lib/surface/call.c#L916)) Error parsing returned status: UNKNOWN
- [x] ([code1](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/1f6faf3725453d45953b2a55feafd7a368f96fff/src/core/lib/security/transport/client_auth_filter.c#L111-L114), [code2](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/1f6faf3725453d45953b2a55feafd7a368f96fff/src/core/lib/security/transport/client_auth_filter.c#L179-L180), [code3](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/1f6faf3725453d45953b2a55feafd7a368f96fff/src/core/lib/security/transport/client_auth_filter.c#L208), transferred to Issue #7182) Incorrect Auth metadata ( Credentials failed to get metadata, Incompatible credentials set on channel and call, Invalid host set in :authority metadata, etc.): UNAUTHENTICATED
- [x] ([code](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/40a3e64aba597760edcdab2d9e95a0304840ebe8/src/objective-c/ProtoRPC/ProtoRPC.m#L51-L53)) Error parsing response proto: INTERNAL

The following error codes are currently generated under certain cases not captured by the document
- [x] ([code](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/a9df5d1029b303a305481c4bb765c6bed2e8ebbb/src/objective-c/GRPCClient/GRPCCall.m#L215-L217), transferred to Issue #7181) The app does not have enough memory to hold the server response: INTERNAL

The following error codes are supposed not to be generated:
- [x]  INVALID_ARGUMENT
- [x]  NOT_FOUND
- [x]  ALREADY_EXISTS
- [x]  FAILED_PRECONDITION
- [x]  ABORTED
- [x]  OUT_OF_RANGE
- [x]  DATA_LOSS
